answers.text: Swift is a type safe language
Swift always chooses Float over Double
Comments are ignored by the Swift compiler
Swift requires you to write a semicolon after each statement
Functions are self-contained chunks of code that perform a specific task.
Global and nested functions, are actually special cases of closures.
Enumeration members are assigned a default integer value when they are created.
The return value of a function can be ignored when it is called
